8.name: large rug
8.short_description: A large rug lies rolled up here.
8.long_description: A large rug is laid out across the grass.

9.name: stone pedestal
9.short_description: Very decorative, and far more pleasant to look at than the gargoyle.
9.long_description: Very decorative, and far more pleasant to look at than the gargoyle.

10.name: ugly gargoyle
10.short_description: Light shines down past the base of the gargoyle.
10.long_description: The base of the gargoyle blocks the ladder upwards completely. I doubt you'll even be able to move it from this side.

11.name: ugly gargoyle
11.short_description: A paticularly gross and ugly-looking gargoyle leers at you from a pedestal surrounded by flagstones.
11.long_description: A paticularly gross and ugly-looking gargoyle leers at you from a pedestal surrounded by flagstones. A flagstone beside the gargoyle has vanished revealing a ladder descending into the depths.

13.name: hidden door
13.long_description: A battered wooden door makes a vain attempt to fill an ivy draped doorway to the west.

14.name: hidden door
14.long_description: A small door, half hidden by ivy, opens eastwards into another garden.

24.name: gravestone
24.short_description: A small battered gravestone protrudes from amongst the weeds.
24.long_description: It bears the inscription 'Squeak The Gerbil', sadly passed away September 92.

31.name: monks bones
31.short_description: A human skeleton, now  picked clean by time.
31.long_description: A skeleton sits here in a full lotus position, grinning at you macabrely.

34.name: ornate door
34.short_description: The door to the rest of the monastery is closed.
34.long_description: The dojo door is closed, allowing you to concentrate on your efforts.

35.name: ornate door
35.short_description: An ornate door stands closed, and through it you can see a very strange room.
35.long_description: A door here stands closed. On it you can read the inscription 'To gain enlightenment, the body must be trained to discipline the mind.'

37.name: monks sandals
37.short_description: A pair of old discarded sandals lie here in a heap.
37.long_description: A pair of sandals, handtooled in soft leather, now sadly old and valueless.

40.name: zen scroll
40.short_description: A scroll lies here, with some strange characters scripted onto it.
40.long_description: A parchment, with fine Calligraphic characters telling something in the secret language of the monks.

41.name: dirty habit
41.short_description: A monks habit is hanging from a peg on the wall.
41.long_description: Someone, ashamed of their dirty habit, has dropped it here.

42.name: old door
42.short_description: A wooden door is open to the south.
42.long_description: A wooden door to the south is shut tight against interference.

43.name: old door
43.short_description: A door to the north lies open.
43.long_description: The wooden door of the cell is firmly shut.

44.name: cell door
44.short_description: With the door closed, the stench of Old Monk is unbearable.

45.name: cell door
45.short_description: The cell door to the west is closed.
45.long_description: The cell door to the west is open, a faint aroma wafting through the opening.

49.name: cell door
49.short_description: The door is closed tight, shutting out the world.
49.long_description: The cell door is closed. It leads out into the gloomy corridor.

50.name: cell door
50.short_description: The cell door nearest you is closed.
50.long_description: The cell door nearest you is closed.

54.name: Temple Curtain
54.short_description: A bale of silken cloth, with finest gold weave, lies here.
54.long_description: This weave is made of purest, softest silk, with a fine gold weave pattern.

55.name: Outer door
55.short_description: The outer door is closed, sealing off the noise and excitement of the outside world.
55.long_description: The outer door stands closed, and through it you catch a glimpse of the rest of the monastery.

56.name: Outer door
56.short_description: The outer door is closed against trespassers.
56.long_description: The outer door is closed, letting you glimpse the treasures within.

59.name: wall
59.short_description: You can't get to the wall underneath all that ivy.
59.long_description: You can't get to the wall underneath all that ivy.

60.name: ivy
60.short_description: The ivy hangs down in a thick tangle, but, lifting it on your arm, you can see a door hidden behind it.
60.long_description: The ivy hangs down in a thick tangle, but, lifting it on your arm, you can see a door hidden behind it.

66.name: mighty wall
66.short_description: The stonework is rough and might possibly be climbed, although it would be far from easy.
66.long_description: The stonework is rough and might possibly be climbed, although it would be far from easy.

69.name: black bottle
69.long_description: A small black bottle lies here. The bottle seems to shake and rattle, as if something very large is trying to get out.

76.name: crystal wand
76.long_description: A delicate crystal wand lies here.

77.name: smelly fish
77.long_description: A smelly fish lies on the ground. The stink wafts up around you making your eyes water.

78.name: black cat
78.short_description: A large black cat stares out at you, its eyes an emerald blaze.
78.long_description: As you stare into the cat's eyes you feel as if you are looking through time far into the past. As if the cat dates back far into prehistory.

88.name: lump of chalk
88.long_description: A small lump of chalk has been left here.

92.name: gold goblet
92.long_description: A gold goblet has been left here.

97.name: stone altar
97.short_description: Carved into the shape of a huge hammer.
97.long_description: Carved into the shape of a huge hammer.

98.name: door
98.long_description: A heavy door, with a strong bolt.

106.name: large axe
106.long_description: A very sharp axe lies here.

107.name: leather jacket
107.long_description: A thick leather jacket lies here.

113.name: old spear
113.long_description: An old spear protrudes from amongst the junk.

114.name: yard of ale
114.long_description: A yard of ale has been left here by some foolish person.

116.name: cauldron
116.long_description: A cauldron of soup sits on the fire.

120.name: large fire
120.long_description: A large smouldering pile of ashes lies here.

124.name: young boy
124.short_description: Sad eyed and lost in thought, the face of a poet.
124.long_description: A young boy sits crosslegged on one of the bigger rocks, gazing far out to sea. As he watches and waits he plays a quiet mournful tune on a set of small pipes. The haunting music forming a beautiful counterpoint to the crashing waves.

149.name: gravestone
149.short_description: The stones are mostly from the last great plague to hit Tranoch some two hundred and thirty years ago. Each worn stone bears a name or two in silent remembrance. Each name gradually vanishing, worn away by old man time himself.
149.long_description: The stones are mostly from the last great plague to hit Tranoch some two hundred and thirty years ago. Each worn stone bears a name or two in silent remembrance. Each name gradually vanishing, worn away by old man time himself.

151.name: gravestone
151.short_description: The stones are mostly from the last great plague to hit Tranoch some two hundred and thirty years ago. Each worn stone bears a name or two in silent remembrance. Each name gradually vanishing, worn away by old man time himself.
151.long_description: The stones are mostly from the last great plague to hit Tranoch some two hundred and thirty years ago. Each worn stone bears a name or two in silent remembrance. Each name gradually vanishing, worn away by old man time himself.

157.name: gallery extension
157.short_description: Plumes of noxious smoke billow up from vents in the floor of the cavern.
157.long_description: Plumes of noxious smoke billow up from vents in the floor of the cavern.

169.name: bronze ingot
169.long_description: A bronze ingot lies on the floor.

170.name: silver ingot
170.long_description: A silver ingot gleams before you.

171.name: gold ingot
171.long_description: A gold ingot gleams before you.

172.name: mithril ingot
172.long_description: A mithril ingot gleams before you.

173.name: hobbit painting
173.short_description: Painting of a hobbit in a small wooden frame.
173.long_description: This painting looks like a portrait of a once legendary adventurer.

174.name: footstool
174.short_description: ; a footstool is adjacent to one
174.long_description: A footstool lies somewhat incongruously here.

175.name: rocking chair
175.long_description: A rocking chair creaks sadly to itself in the corner.

177.name: small candle
177.long_description: There is a small candle here.

180.name: secret door
180.short_description: A narrow door leads south. The door is shut.
180.long_description: It fits tightly to the frame. Whether it is visible to anyone on the other side of the wall is doubtful.

181.name: secret panel
181.long_description: A panel in the north wall hangs slightly open.

182.name: religious text
182.short_description: A small thin religious text lies here, its pages flapping in the faint draught.
182.long_description: It would seem to be a copy of the apocryphal Acts of Nimicus - rare, and possibly valuable, but now frequently regarded as evidence of heresy.

187.name: mint
187.long_description: A string of mint has spread itself across the garden.

188.name: garlic
188.long_description: A complete bulb - should be enough to keep half of Transylvania at bay...

190.name: white book
190.short_description: A white book is fastened to the shelves.
190.long_description: Bound in finest calfskin this old book is a detailed work on magic and the magicial arts, within its pages are detailed such spells as 'cure','where', and combat spells such as 'fireball', 'missile' and 'shock', as well as the nature combat spell 'electrify'.

191.name: dark libram
191.short_description: A dark libram lies on the shelf, securely chained down.
191.long_description: A dark and evil work, bound in flayed human skin. It is a turgid learned tome, detailing the evil priest powers, and in paticular their unusual properties of needing deaths to cast magic, and of the lack of effect of iron on their magic. It also briefly mentions 'zombie' and 'produce flame', the most well known of the evil priestly powers.

192.name: oak door
192.long_description: The oak door to the east is closed and leads through into the library.

193.name: oak door
193.long_description: The oak door is closed, and leads west through into the work room.

194.name: ephemeris
194.short_description: An ephemeris is firmly chained to the bookcases.
194.long_description: A worn and battered volume, chained firmly to the bookcases. The contents deal with astrological significance of the stars, which as everyone knows are small jewels in the sky.

196.name: brass candelabrum
196.long_description: A brass candelabrum stands on the south side of the altar.

197.name: athame
197.long_description: A razor sharp athame rests on the eastern edge of the altar.

198.name: golden goblet
198.short_description: A golden goblet glitters before you.
198.long_description: A golden goblet stands on the western side of the altar.

199.name: smelly incense
199.long_description: A stick of incense has been left here. Judging by the smell the owner finally had enough of it.

200.name: sand
200.short_description: A small heap of fine sand.
200.long_description: A small heap of sand sits on the north side of the altar.

201.name: carved runes
201.short_description: Deeply mystic, but no doubt purely decorative.
201.long_description: Deeply mystic, but no doubt purely decorative.

202.name: stone altar
202.short_description: A sense of deep power and awareness seems to flow from the altar.
202.long_description: A stone altar stands in the centre of the room, surrounded by a magic circle woven into the carpets.

203.name: ornate mirror
203.short_description: A very high quality mirror, with a beautiful frame of carved wood.
203.long_description: A very high quality mirror, with a beautiful frame of carved wood.

207.name: clothes chest
207.long_description: A clothes chest sits here. The chest is open.

208.name: oak table
208.long_description: A stout oak table stands next to the bed.

209.name: full-height mirror
209.short_description: A very high quality mirror, with a beautiful frame of carved wood.
209.long_description: A very high quality mirror, with a beautiful frame of carved wood.

212.name: oak door
212.long_description: A heavy oak door bars entry to the tower.

222.name: bee hive
222.short_description: Large, with a sticky sweet smell coming from it.
222.long_description: A large squat beehive stands here, with bees dancing in the air around it. The hive is open.

224.name: tatty box
224.long_description: On a shelf at about shoulder-height lies an old box.

225.name: small hatchet
225.short_description: There is a small but useful hatchet lying here.
225.long_description: Excellent for chopping down trees, and possibly useful on people too.

226.name: strong bucket
226.short_description: A sturdy bucket, with a metal handle.
226.long_description: A bucket has been left lying about here.

227.name: stone gates
227.long_description: The gates stand firmly shut, barring any entry.

228.name: stone gates
228.long_description: The gates stand firmly shut, barring any egress.

229.name: iron chain
229.short_description: Good solid chain, unweakened despite years of rusting.
229.long_description: A heavy iron chain hangs down from the hole in the roof.

230.name: small note
230.short_description: A small note is stuck on the door.
230.long_description: The note reads 'Gone questing, back in five years.'

237.name: fountain pump
237.short_description: An iron pump, which can be moved up and down.
237.long_description: An iron pump is set into the floor here, its handle pushed down.

241.name: fountain pipes
241.short_description: A system of pipes run along the garden to supply the water for the fountains. They seem still to be in working order, but the controlling mechanism for them does not seem to be apparent.
241.long_description: A system of pipes run along the garden to supply the water for the fountains. They seem still to be in working order, but the controlling mechanism for them does not seem to be apparent.

242.name: arching fountains
242.short_description: A system of pipes run along the garden to supply the water for these fountains. They seem still to be in working order, but the controlling mechanism for them does not seem to be apparent.
242.long_description: You are in a garden which is bounded by ivy-covered walls to the north and east and bushy hedgerow to the south and west. You can cross through the hedges but the walls are too high to climb. A mist of spray covers the whole of this section of garden. It originates with the fountains lining the edges of the garden, filling your eyes with all the colours of the spectrum and soaking you from head to foot.

244.name: filigree key
244.long_description: A filigree key lies half-hidden on the ground.

245.name: old music
245.short_description: A piece of old music lies here.
245.long_description: The music is old and faded, and has been repaired many times.

246.name: silver flute
246.long_description: A small flute has carelessly been left here.

247.name: decaying rushes
247.long_description: Rushes are strewn over the floor.

248.name: black cloth
248.long_description: An old piece of black cloth lies here.

249.name: Relia's portrait
249.short_description: A black cloth hangs over what is presumably a portrait.
249.long_description: A splendid and costly portrait is propped up here, showing a very beautiful woman sitting in front of a clavichord. She is smiling at someone out of the picture.

250.name: sea chart
250.short_description: A chart lies here, curling at the corners.
250.long_description: This chart shows the eastern coastline and a large island off the coast. A faint tracing shows where someone has failed to rub out all of a possible route between them.

251.name: Birfle's invitation
251.short_description: An invitation has been dropped here.
251.long_description: This beautifully-written note reads: 'Dear Morran, it is some time since I last had the pleasure of seeing you and Relia. I have recently acquired some items I believe you would be delighted to see, in particular a most excellent specimen of Draco Veritas, or the true dragon. I should like to invite you both to my island for a stay in which we can catch up on old times.'

252.name: artist's receipt
252.short_description: A small receipt lies before you.
252.long_description: This paper bears the message 'Thanking you for your recent commission to paint your most beautiful wife at her favourite instrument. The challenge to convey her loveliness will be my delight.' It is dated some ten years previously.

253.name: Morran's papers
253.short_description: The papers reflect the declining years of a busy merchant. They are in some disorder, as if abandoned before they had been dealt with.
253.long_description: The papers reflect the declining years of a busy merchant. They are in some disorder, as if abandoned before they had been dealt with.

254.name: Morran's desk
254.short_description: An old desk stands under the window.
254.long_description: The desk is strewn with papers and junk.

255.name: lyre
255.short_description: A lyre hangs here on the wall.
255.long_description: A lyre lies here, its strings humming in the draught.

257.name: old fireplace
257.short_description: The fireplace is more for ornament than use, with decorative mouldings in the corner of which are inscribed the words 'Morran had me made'.
257.long_description: The fireplace is more for ornament than use, with decorative mouldings in the corner of which are inscribed the words 'Morran had me made'.

258.name: broken shards
258.short_description: Millions of pieces of shattered glass and china.
258.long_description: Millions of shards of broken glass litter the floor.

261.name: glass cabinet
261.short_description: A cabinet made from glass stands here.
261.long_description: A cabinet made from glass stands here, the door hanging open.

262.name: iron key
262.long_description: A door key of some kind.

263.name: couch
263.short_description: Most refreshing for visitors to sink into.
263.long_description: Most refreshing for visitors to sink into.

268.name: east door
268.short_description: The door through to the remainder of the house is closed.
268.long_description: A cobweb in the corner of a panel in the door shows how little-used it is.

269.name: dusty door
269.long_description: The door leading back to the gallery is closed.

271.name: musty door
271.long_description: Woodworm has not improved this door's smell.

272.name: west door
272.long_description: Woodworm has not improved this door's smell.

275.name: mahogany door
275.short_description: The mahogany door is firmly closed.
275.long_description: The mahogany door is closed, leading through to the chart room.

276.name: mahogany door
276.long_description: The mahogany door is closed, leading through to the music room.

280.name: plain door
280.long_description: The plain door is tightly closed.

281.name: plain door
281.long_description: The plain door is tightly closed.

285.name: west door
285.long_description: The door into the house is closed.

288.name: rusted gates
288.short_description: A pair of gates westwards are closed.
288.long_description: The gates are old and worn, hanging from their hinges sadly. With a little effort, they can probably be shifted a few feet.

289.name: rusted gates
289.short_description: A pair of rusted gates lean against each other, blocking your road out.
289.long_description: The gates are old and worn, hanging from their hinges sadly. With a little effort, they can probably be shifted a few feet.

294.name: gold crown
294.long_description: A golden crown lies on top of the tomb.

295.name: massive tomb
295.short_description: A huge sealed tomb sits in the centre of the chamber.
295.long_description: Huge and heavy. Sealed rock, and immovable. It bears the inscription 'Here lies Mighty King Isldor, and his queen Harian, who gave her life to be with him in death'.

296.name: stone slab
296.long_description: A huge solid stone slab. Certainly immovable from this side.

297.name: stone slab
297.long_description: Heavy and strong, but possibly openable.

318.name: black cloak
318.long_description: A long and fine jet black cloak.

322.name: huge ruby
322.short_description: A huge ruby lies on the ground here.
322.long_description: It is the blood-red heart of the golden dragon.

323.name: library book
323.short_description: A battered book has been dropped here.
323.long_description: A battered book has been dropped here.

326.name: necronomicon
326.short_description: A copy of the dread necronomicon sits on the pillar.
326.long_description: A copy of the necronomicon lies darkly before you, its pages bound in flayed human skin.

327.name: black casket
327.long_description: A black casket lies here. It is open.

329.name: candle
329.long_description: A black candle stands here. It is lit.

345.name: monolith
345.short_description: A huge stone of ancient origin. Narrow steps are cut into the stone.
345.long_description: A huge stone of ancient origin. Narrow steps are cut into the stone.

370.name: sack
370.short_description: It looks like quite a strong sack.
370.long_description: A sack marked 'Dragon Food' has been dumped here. Someone has left it open.

371.name: crystal goblet
371.long_description: A large crystal goblet full of wine has been left here.

372.name: leather leash
372.short_description: A name tag on the collar reads 'Tiddles'.
372.long_description: An enormous leather leash hangs up on a hook on the wall.

373.name: sliding panel
373.short_description: It has a small handle at one end.
373.long_description: A small sliding panel is set into the east wall. It is open.

374.name: lump of meat
374.short_description: It seems to still be fresh, somehow.
374.long_description: A large lump of meat has been dropped here.

381.name: large pavillion
381.long_description: A large pavillion has been erected in the centre of the clearing.

387.name: clock bottom
387.short_description: There is an closed trapdoor set in the floor.
387.long_description: There is an closed trapdoor set in the floor.

389.name: crystal decanter
389.short_description: A large crystal decanter has been placed here.
389.long_description: A large, heavy, carved crystal decanter, with gold fittings.

390.name: bottle of wine
390.short_description: It is a bottle of fine vintage claret.
390.long_description: A large bottle of wine has been left here.

404.name: iron poker
404.short_description: A long iron poker lies here.

408.name: sharp axe
408.short_description: A sharp axe is embedded in the wall.
408.long_description: Short handled, but extremely sharp and heavy. The manufacture is of noteworthy quality.

409.name: brass lantern
409.long_description: A brass lantern lies here, its flame throwing a flickering pattern on the ground.

414.name: dusty book
414.short_description: A large, dusty book has been left here.
414.long_description: The sands of Time have been flowing around this book for many years.

425.name: large book
425.short_description: A large book has been left here.
425.long_description: A large book has been left here. It is open.

426.name: barrels
426.long_description: The barrels have been moved, revealing an exit east.

437.name: pendulum
437.short_description: The pendulum hangs straight down, and is still.
437.long_description: It is connected to the inner workings of the clock.

438.name: weight
438.short_description: It is a large, iron weight.
438.long_description: A large weight has been dropped here.

439.name: clock door
439.short_description: It is the door of the grandfather clock.
439.long_description: It is the door of the grandfather clock.

440.name: clock door
440.short_description: It is the door of the grandfather clock.
440.long_description: It is the door of the grandfather clock.

441.name: grandfather clock
441.short_description: A grandfather clock stands in the corner.
441.long_description: It is a tall, polished, wooden grandfather clock. You notice that it has only got one hand.

445.name: wooden box
445.short_description: It is a dilapidated old wooden tea chest.
445.long_description: A small, wooden box has been placed on a shelf.

449.name: dreaming tower
449.short_description: It is a huge building, vast in scale.
449.long_description: The dreaming tower stands before you. A single archway leads into the tower.

450.name: light
450.short_description: It sits there and glows oddly and faintly.
450.long_description: A faint patch of glowing light hangs in the air.

465.name: shadow
465.short_description: A sort of darkish patch on light.
465.long_description: A sort of darkish patch on light.

466.name: shadow
466.short_description: A sort of darkish patch on light.
466.long_description: A sort of darkish patch on light.

467.name: shadow
467.short_description: A sort of darkish patch on light.
467.long_description: A sort of darkish patch on light.

469.name: heavy mace
469.short_description: An old mace has been left here.
469.long_description: A long, heavy, iron mace, studded at the business end, so as to inflict even more damage.

470.name: quartz
470.long_description: A large lump of quartz lies here.

471.name: iron chain
471.short_description: It hangs down from the roof.
471.long_description: A long corroded iron chain hangs down from a small hole in the roof.

474.name: handle
474.long_description: There is a small wooden handle in the wall, next to the hole.

475.name: stove
475.short_description: It is black with grime, and stone cold.
475.long_description: There is a small, wood burning stove in the corner, which is only big enough for the smallest snacks.

476.name: hole
476.short_description: It looks like the hole for a dumb waiter.
476.long_description: It looks like the hole for a dumb waiter.

478.name: hole
478.short_description: and a hole in the east wall.
478.long_description: It looks like the hole for a dumb waiter.

479.name: dead cat
479.short_description: There is a dead cat here.
479.long_description: It has used up all nine of its lives.

486.name: lump of chalk
486.short_description: A small lump of chalk has been left here.
486.long_description: A small piece of white chalk, it has a vaguely human shape. You have a nasty feeling that this is all that remains of the last person to come this way...

488.name: lump of chalk
488.short_description: A small piece of natural white chalk.
488.long_description: A small lump of chalk has been left here.

490.name: silver cross
490.short_description: A large silver cross has been dropped here.
490.long_description: It is a large, ornate, silver cross on a chain.

491.name: steaming liquid
491.short_description: The bath is full of liquid.
491.long_description: The bath is full of a steaming liquid.

492.name: tin bath
492.short_description: A tin bath has been pushed against the wall.
492.long_description: There is a tin bath here. It has been pulled away from the wall slightly.

493.name: large desk
493.short_description: There is a large desk in the middle of the room.
493.long_description: It fills most of the room, and is covered by a thick layer of dust.

494.name: bloodstained bible
494.short_description: A bloodstained bible has been dropped here.
494.long_description: It is a standard bible, containing both testaments and the Book of Mormon.

498.name: iron maiden
498.short_description: An iron maiden stands against the east wall.
498.long_description: An iron maiden stands against the east wall. It is open.

501.name: old cupboard
501.short_description: There is an old cupboard here.
501.long_description: It is a rough old wooden cupboard. There are blood stains on the door.

503.name: wooden coffin
503.short_description: It is a rough wooden box, 6 feet long and 3 feet wide.
503.long_description: A rough wooden coffin has been left lying underneath the table. It is open.

504.name: huge key
504.short_description: A huge, iron key has been dropped here.
504.long_description: A huge, iron key hangs up on a hook by the iron door.

505.name: large table
505.short_description: It is a very solid, old wooden table.
505.long_description: There is a large table in the middle of the room.

506.name: red robe
506.short_description: A red robe hangs up on the wall.
506.long_description: It is a large robe, coloured red to hide the stains.

508.name: small bag
508.short_description: It is a small, hessian bag.
508.long_description: A small bag has been placed in the corner of the room.

509.name: flaying knife
509.short_description: A flaying knife has been left here.
509.long_description: It is razor sharp, and stained with dried blood.

512.name: iron door
512.short_description: There is an iron door in the south wall.
512.long_description: It is a very sturdy iron door, with a barred window in it.

566.long_description: However hard you search, you dont seem to be able to find his head.

643.name: names
643.short_description: One name that catches your eye is 'Anarchy The Wizard'. Beside it is written 'Even I clutch at the straws of immortality, not for the fear of dying but for the fear of being forgotten.'
643.long_description: One name that catches your eye is 'Anarchy The Wizard'. Beside it is written 'Even I clutch at the straws of immortality, not for the fear of dying but for the fear of being forgotten.'

644.name: extension
644.long_description: feeling of preservation. At the same time there is a mocking sense of sadness at the futility of human endeavour, and the knowledge that one day even the temple will pass to dust.

646.name: wizened man
646.short_description: He looks very sad indeed.. loaded with the cares and memories of a world filled with pain.
646.long_description: The wizened old man stands quietly in the shadows, pain filled eyes gazing out across the world. As you walk past he turns and looks forlornly at you. In an unsteady voice he says 'So many to remember, and so much of it is sad. Alas even I can remember them all no longer.'

648.name: fountain

648.long_description: A crystal clear fountain plays gently over a beautiful carved nymph in the centre of the courtyard. The carving is exquisite and must have taken a master many years of labour.

661.name: ancient writings

661.long_description: Most of what is written is illegible to you, but you can just make out the words 'birfle' and 'squidge'.

739.long_description: A blood red rock, smooth as ice and just as chilling...

795.long_description: A jet black scythe, which you could easily imagine helping poor souls to the afterlife...

805.long_description: It is truly beautiful, but seems to be carved from the ice as a whole, and therefore it not easily removable.

835.long_description: Probably used as a marker or store. It appears to have been disturbed recently.

838.name: torn page
838.short_description: A torn page lies on the floor.
838.long_description: Its reads 'and beware for the nature priests have power over storms and the eyes of the world. They posess magiks such as 'where','cure', and most feared of all the magik they name 'electrify' that calls lightning bolts down from the sky. They are the enemy of darkness and all things un-natural. For all this their power wanes, and most of their greatness, like that of the dark priests, is lost .'

845.name: white heather
845.short_description: Some white heather is growing here.
845.long_description: White heather is rumoured to be magical, or to give luck.

868.name: writing
868.short_description: The words 'In memory of all who died in the great mining accident here in 368, may the Gods guard their souls and the people never forget', are carved into the rock.
868.long_description: The words 'In memory of all who died in the great mining accident here in 368, may the Gods guard their souls and the people never forget', are carved into the rock.

870.name: gold nugget

873.name: old ladder
873.short_description: A wooden ladder descends through a shaft in the floor, carefully screened on three sides to prevent people from falling in.
873.long_description: Although very damp, the ladder doesn't seem to have rotted far enough to become dangerous. It is always hard to be sure however.

876.name: skeleton
876.short_description: A partially complete skeleton lies here.
876.long_description: A skeleton sticks out of the bog to the west, the legs and lower torso invisible beneath the soft mud. Fortunately you can still reach the skeleton from here without straying onto the really dangerous looking bits.

885.name: pool
885.long_description: The pool is stagnant and the smell is enough to make your eyes water. Hundreds of flies and other insects swarm across the water in great clouds.

888.name: bush
888.long_description: The bushes are thick and almost imprenetrable.

900.long_description: A heavy stone slab blocks the tunnel southwards.

901.name: heavy slab
901.long_description: A heavy stone slab blocks the passage north.

905.long_description: A small leather bag has been put here.

906.long_description: The chest is heavy and metal bound. It has been carefully sealed with lead for some reason.

907.name: apple
907.long_description: A fresh looking apple has been left here.

908.name: brass telescope

910.short_description: A massive oaken staff has been put here by someone.
910.long_description: It bears the runes of High Lord Anarchy... I wouldn't touch it.

912.long_description: There is a hole underneath the cart, that you might be able squeeze through.

914.long_description: A set of fairly fresh looking sandwiches have been dumped here.

921.long_description: It appears to be very stiff, and probably hasn't been moved for a long time.

924.name: glowing orb

924.long_description: A glowing white orb pulsates before you.

925.name: black rod

926.long_description: A huge moonstone lies in front of you.

927.long_description: A shimmering crystalline bridge spans the lava.

928.long_description: A shimmering crystalline bridge spans the lava.

934.short_description: I'm not sure it's much use here...
934.long_description: A stagecomm pass has been dropped here.

936.long_description: The huge metal plates which form it are hot, and seem to have been exposed to scorching heat quite often.

937.name: massive drawbridge

937.long_description: A massive metal drawbridge is drawn up across a wide archway on the far side of the channel.

939.name: light veil
939.short_description: A beautiful light veil has been left here.
939.long_description: The veil is incredibly fine and spun from the softest of silks.

959.name: sturdy axe

960.name: heavy axe
960.short_description: A heavy axe is stacked here.
960.long_description: Short handled, but extremely sharp and heavy. The manufacture is of noteworthy quality.

961.name: small door
961.short_description: There is a door to the south.
961.long_description: A small door leads south out of the chamber into a low passage.

962.name: small door
962.short_description: The door is about dwarf sized.
962.long_description: There is a small door to the north.

973.name: stick
973.long_description: A long broken branch has been left here.

975.name: ice pendant
975.short_description: A small and beautiful pendant lies here.
975.long_description: A small and beautiful pendant, carved with the runes for invocation and shielding.

979.name: waybread
979.short_description: Some waybread has been put here.

980.name: waybread
980.short_description: Some waybread has been put here.

981.name: small shield
981.long_description: A small shield has been dropped here.

989.name: pie
989.long_description: A small, appetising hobbit pie has been left here.

990.name: loaf
990.long_description: A fresh loaf has been left here.

997.long_description: A hole leads down under the statue.

1014.name: garland
1014.long_description: A beautiful garland has been left against the monolith.

1015.long_description: An ancient standing stone, which some say has mystical powers. Parts of the stone are worn smooth, from countless people touching its surface.

1016.name: stick

1017.long_description: An old broken branch has been dropped here.

1031.name: ripped silk

1031.long_description: A small piece of ripped silk has been left here.

1036.name: flame
1036.long_description: A small magical flame flickers before you.

1037.name: sign

1037.long_description: It reads 'As suppliers of drinks and for our sponsorship of the creation of this universe the owners of this inn are granted total immunity to violence. Customers please take note.'

1040.name: handle

1040.long_description: A wooden handle, for raising water from the well.

1065.long_description: You can just about squeeze south over a large boulder.

1072.name: rotten door
1072.long_description: You can go west through a broken down door.

1080.name: red wand

1081.name: wooden door
1081.long_description: A door stands closed to the south.

1091.name: pillar

1093.name: powerstone

1093.long_description: A pulsating magical powerstone lies here, glowing gently.

1095.name: chip of rock

1095.long_description: A small chip of rock lies on the floor.

1100.name: branch

1114.long_description: A small but beautiful rose has been left here, slowly wilting away.

1117.name: roofing lead

1117.long_description: A neat pile of roofing lead has been left stacked in a corner.

1119.name: golden weathercock
1119.short_description: Even through broken, it is beautiful.
1119.long_description: A golden weathercock has been left here, somewhat out of order.

1124.name: gold cross
1124.long_description: A hefty gold cross lies sparkling before you.

1141.name: stone pitcher
1141.long_description: A pitcher full of water has been placed here.

1149.name: wraith

1149.long_description: A hideous shade of ancient evil, which legend has it can only be touched by silver or magical weapons.

1150.name: withered mummy
1150.long_description: A withered mummy lies upon the stone slab in the centre of the chamber.

1153.name: iron casket

1153.long_description: A stout iron casket, of a type often used to store valuables.

1154.name: wooden chest
1154.long_description: A stout wooden chest lies closed in a corner.

1157.name: runic staff
1157.short_description: Someone has left a long runic staff here.
1157.long_description: The staff is carved with many runes, and its end is a hideous sharpened hooked claw.

1158.name: silver pentacle

1159.long_description: The door is marked with the runes for protection and barring.

1160.name: runic door
1160.short_description: The door is marked with the runes for protection and barring.
1160.long_description: A runic door is set into an arched entrance leading eastwards. The door is open.

1164.name: obsidian pillar
1164.short_description: A tall obsidian pillar stands beside the pool.
1164.long_description: The pillar is marked will many deep, and very large sucker marks.

1166.name: pool
1166.long_description: The pool is murky dark and still, what lies beneath is unknown, and perhaps best that way.

1169.name: obsidian slab
1169.short_description: Ominously the slab stands open. A large pulsating gem is set into the centre of the door.
1169.long_description: The slab is intricately rune carved, with a single empty eye socket at its centre. By the look of the eye socket, it must once have held a very large gem.

1170.name: obsidian slab
1170.long_description: The slab bears a carved image of a man being hurled into a fire.

1172.name: pile of stones
1172.short_description: In amongst the stones a narrow stairwell descends into darkness.
1172.long_description: As you peer in amongst the stones you realise they are covering some form of way downwards.

1188.name: large clam
1188.short_description: A large clam is stuck onto the rocks.
1188.long_description: It is fastened securely onto the rocks. On closer examination you realise that it is an oyster not a clam.

1193.name: soap
1193.short_description: A piece of old soap has been left here.
1193.long_description: Very dirty, it wouldn't help clean anything now.

1194.name: old door
1194.long_description: You peer at the remarkable achievement of science.

1195.name: old door
1195.short_description: Haven't you seen a door before ?
1195.long_description: An open door leads south into a corridor.

1199.name: scarred shelves
1199.long_description: Anything of any value has been burned away.

1201.name: oak door
1201.long_description: The doors appear to have been struck by some kind of magical forces.

1202.name: oak table
1202.short_description: A small oak table stands here.
1202.long_description: Mystic symbols are inlaid into its top, along with a draught board.

1204.name: shadowy figure
1204.short_description: The figure has a menacing, powerful air.
1204.long_description: A tall figure stands in front of the oak doors, gazing at you through baleful glowing eyes.

1206.name: piece of pumice
1206.short_description: A piece of pumice lies before you.
1206.long_description: The rock is light and full of bubbles.

1207.name: fragment of obsidian
1207.long_description: A jagged fragment of obsidian lies here.

1210.name: glowing crystal
1210.short_description: A large crystal has been left here.
1210.long_description: The crystal is obviously magical, but you are astounded to see the symbol of Haze, probably the greatest (and most evil) sorceror ever to walk the world, engraved upon its surface.

1211.name: wooden ladder
1211.short_description: It leads down into the main part of the storehouse.
1211.long_description: It leads down into the main part of the storehouse.

1213.name: hay
1213.short_description: Loads of it, I hope you don't get hayfever...
1213.long_description: Loads of it, I hope you don't get hayfever...

1216.name: strong horse
1216.long_description: A strong lean horse stands here.

1217.name: pitchfork
1217.short_description: A long and rather sharp pitchfork glints in the light.
1217.long_description: A farming implement, but rather effective on people too.

1224.name: wooden crate
1224.short_description: An open wooden crate has been left here.
1224.long_description: The crate is suffering from the effects of age and damp, but like all such seagoing material, it is so stout and strong that it will last for many a year yet.

1230.name: black altar
1230.short_description: You study the altar, and its strange carvings. As you follow the carvings your mind seems to be coming under some kind of hypnotic control. Horrified you tear your eyes away.
1230.long_description: You study the altar, and its strange carvings. As you follow the carvings your mind seems to be coming under some kind of hypnotic control. Horrified you tear your eyes away.

1231.name: dark shroud
1231.long_description: The shrouds are incredibly dark, and seem to be sticky, as if soaked in blood. Behind one of the shrouds are the words 'Know me, the fire, the blood that burns in sacrifice. Serve me and I grant you the power to produce flame, and the power of zombie in return for blood. Serve me right or burn forever.'

1232.name: red crystals
1232.short_description: The crystals are glowing very dimly.
1232.long_description: The crystals glare an intense actinic red. Above the altar, now shrouded in intense light, a manlike figure is beginning to appear.

1234.name: crumbling scroll
1234.short_description: A musty crumbling scroll has been placed here.
1234.long_description: The scroll is dusty and hard to read, but it bears the words 'Let those who can read these symbols know that this is the third incarnation of the world, and let him be wise to the history of the world. It is said that the first age of the world was the age of dwarves and dragons, when the black sword was forged, the second age was the age of war, where magicians and warriors fought for power. The third age will be the age of power for the magic is strong again.'

1238.name: dark robe
1238.short_description: A very long dark robe lies here, stretched out full length.
1238.long_description: Two silver lightning bolts are etched in gold thread down the back.

1239.name: old robe
1239.long_description: An old robe lies in a heap, collecting dust.

1240.name: black robe
1240.short_description: A tatty black robe has been dropped here.
1240.long_description: It has holes in it, but is still basically sound.

1243.name: stone statue
1243.short_description: The statue is carved into the likeness of a man, with deep staring eyes.
1243.long_description: A huge stone statue stands on one side of the entrance, its sinister empty eyes glaring towards you.

1245.name: yard of ale
1245.long_description: A yard of ale has been left here by some foolish person.

1246.name: brass lantern
1246.long_description: A brass lantern has been left here, its wan light flickering gently.

1251.name: old shields
1251.long_description: Remnants of ancient heroes and glories.

1255.name: huge crystal
1255.long_description: You gaze into the crystal for a while, but even your finely honed mind cannot follow the action within.

1256.name: small door
1256.long_description: It leads to the chamber of the arch-magi

1257.name: gold door
1257.long_description: It bears the runes for World and Holding.

1258.name: mighty door
1258.long_description: The mighty doors stand open to the south.

1266.name: old runes
1266.long_description: The runes are difficult to follow and decipher, but seem to be directions to some of the arcane magical arts, and detail some of the movements to be associated with spells.

1269.name: small well
1269.long_description: It appears to have dried up.

1274.name: stone coffin
1274.short_description: It bears the words 'Open not, lest foul undead slay thee.'
1274.long_description: A stone coffin is set on a plinth in the centre of the chamber. The coffin is open.

1276.name: old dust
1276.long_description: The thick dust on the floor shows you are the only person to have come this way for a long time.

1280.name: dilapidated door
1280.long_description: The door is old and battered, worn by the weather and by time.

1281.name: wooden sign
1281.long_description: It is battered and has seen too many years exposure to the driving salt soaked winds that howl in from the sea.

1284.name: spit
1284.long_description: A pig roasts on a spit above the roaring fire.

1291.name: sack
1291.short_description: An old rather rotten looking sack has been dumped here.
1291.long_description: It seems in better condition than at first sight, but it is still not in great condition.

1293.name: large window
1293.short_description: A huge window looks out across the snows.
1293.long_description: It looks out over the snows. You could climb out of the window and down the snowbanks outside, providing of course they will take your weight. It is difficult to tell if they will though.

1295.name: large window
1295.short_description: You could climb up and through it quite easily.
1295.long_description: A large window is set high up above the snowbanks on one side.

1296.name: stone tablet
1296.short_description: An ancient stone tablet has been left here.
1296.long_description: The tablet is an ancient piece from the philosopher-mage Theosynimus. It bears the words 'Thrice at the lich-owl's screech, cast fire into the images of the moon, listen well lest bitter experience teach, none make the path of the shadow alone.'

1299.name: small rock
1299.short_description: A small piece of rock lies here.
1299.long_description: A small piece of rock has been left on a stone slab.

1300.name: hammer
1300.short_description: A heavy mining hammer has been left here.
1300.long_description: Very heavy, not the sort of hammer to hit your fingers with, more for hitting other peoples.

1301.name: pick
1301.long_description: A heavy pick has been put here. The pick is battered and worn, and obviously much used.

1304.name: quarry shed
1304.short_description: It appears to be a store for all the quarrying equipment.
1304.long_description: A large stone built shed stands at the north end of the quarry.

1316.name: still pool
1316.long_description: The gentle swaying of the trees, and their reflection in the pool, make this place seem quiet and peaceful.

1322.name: old fire
1322.short_description: The fire is quite old, several days at least.
1322.long_description: Someone has had a fire here recently, although all that is left now is a pile of ashes. Someone has spread the ashes out too.

1324.name: portable hole
1324.short_description: There is a large hole here.
1324.long_description: It is a strange hole. It seems almost well, unattached.

1328.name: mystic talisman
1328.short_description: It appears to be a marker for some kind of magic.
1328.long_description: An ancient engraved stone talisman has been placed here.

1329.name: large tomb
1329.short_description: The tomb is very solidly built from stone slabs.
1329.long_description: A large stone tomb is set in the very centre of the chamber. The tomb is open.

1340.name: wooden boat
1340.long_description: An old wooden boat has been left here.

1343.name: icy passage
1343.short_description: An icy passage has been hacked through the icy wall, leading north into a cave.
1343.long_description: An icy passage has been hacked through the icy wall, leading north into a cave.

1345.name: icy passage
1345.short_description: An icy passage has been hacked through the snowy walls of the cave, to reveal a huge icy hall extending away southwards.
1345.long_description: An icy passage has been hacked through the snowy walls of the cave, to reveal a huge icy hall extending away southwards.

1347.name: frozen corpse
1347.long_description: A stiff and frozen human corpse lies slumped on the ground.

1348.name: narrow cavemouth
1348.long_description: The opening appears to lead into a cave.

1349.name: icy cavemouth
1349.long_description: The cavemouth is blocked up by a huge fall of snow.

1351.name: piles of snow
1351.long_description: The snow is deep and movement awkward. There appears to have been an avalanche here recently. A narrow path leads east and steeply up into a side valley.

1353.name: wooden bridge
1353.long_description: Across the bridge the path continues south along the other side of the pass.

1355.name: old bridge
1355.long_description: An old wooden bridge carries the path westwards across the foaming waters onto the other side of the pass. The bridge looks in good condition, and is probably fairly safe. If not then its a long way to fall into foaming ice cold water....

1366.name: shortsword
1366.long_description: A sharp shortsword has been dropped here.

1367.name: small dagger
1367.short_description: Although small it is very sharp.
1367.long_description: A small dagger has been dropped here.

1371.name: old horseshoe
1371.short_description: Well it didnt bring the horse any luck.
1371.long_description: An old horseshoe has been discarded here.

1374.name: runesword
1374.short_description: A huge black runesword lies at your feet, glowing with arcane power.
1374.long_description: A huge black runesword stands upright before you, embedded in the solid stone altar.

1378.name: iron lever
1378.short_description: It is connected to a mass of heavy mechanisms.
1378.long_description: A huge iron lever in the west wall has been pulled right back in its slot.

1379.name: oak door
1379.long_description: An open oak door leads east into the gatehouse.

1382.name: strong portcullis
1382.short_description: It is strong and bound in heavy iron.
1382.long_description: The portcullis is raised, allowing free access to and from the castle.

1384.name: portcullis
1384.long_description: It is strong and bound in heavy iron.

1385.name: red hat
1385.long_description: The red fedora hat looks about your size.

1386.name: wizard hat
1386.long_description: The wizard hat is tall, with a large floppy brim.

1387.name: witch hat
1387.long_description: The witch hat is black and tall, with a large round brim.

1388.name: granite statue
1388.long_description: The ominous black granite statue in the shape of a giant penguin casts a long stadow down the hall. Its surface is smooth and polished.
